subject: HISTORY
text: Explain and compare the Athenian and Spartan systems of government on the eve of the Peloponnesian War.

subject: HISTORY
text: Trace the steps by which Philip of Macedon became the master of Greece, and explain the ease with which he did so.

subject: HISTORY
text: What were the social and political objects of the Gracchi? What results had their efforts?

subject: HISTORY
text: Trace briefly the growth of the Roman Empire between the death of Augustus and that of Trajan.

subject: HISTORY
text: Write notes on two of the following: Solon, the Persian invasion of Greece in (490 b.c.), Dionysius of Syracuse, Cato the Censor, Sulla, the Second Triumvirate.

subject: HISTORY
text: Account for the rise of Continental feudalism and show what were its main features.

subject: HISTORY
text: What services did Philip II (Augustus) render to France?

subject: HISTORY
text: Do you agree with the view that Frederick II was the last of the great Holy Roman Emperors?

subject: HISTORY
text: Explain the causes and effects of the Great Schism of the Papacy (1378-1414).

subject: HISTORY
text: Write notes on two of the following: Charlemagne, the First Crusade, the Franciscan Friars, the Lombard League, the Sicilian Vespers, the Hussites.

subject: HISTORY
text: On what grounds may Charles VIII's invasion of Italy be said to mark the beginning of modern Europe?

subject: HISTORY
text: Describe the origins and account for the success of the Reformation movement in Germany.

subject: HISTORY
text: What problems faced Henry IV of France on his accession, and how far did he succeed in solving them?

subject: HISTORY
text: Why is the Peace of Westphalia an important landmark in the history of Europe?

subject: HISTORY
text: What do you understand by the Diplomatic Revolution of (1756)? How did it come about?

subject: HISTORY
text: “A ruler of lofty ideals who died a complete failure.” Discuss this estimate of Emperor Joseph II.

subject: HISTORY
text: Do you consider that Napoleon was greater as a general or as a constructive statesman at home?

subject: HISTORY
text: Compare the methods of Bismarck and Cavour in the unification of Germany and Italy.

subject: HISTORY
text: Why were the Balkans the storm centre of Europe during the years (1908-1914)?

subject: HISTORY
text: Write notes on two of the following: Catherine II of Russia, the French Directory, the Congress of Verona, the Peace of Paris (1856), Leon Gambetta, the Algeciras Conference.
